    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-10-22T00:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-10-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="755"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d755">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">867N.01/10–2245: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Iraq</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Moreland</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="80" xml:id="d755fn80">Marginal notation by the Secretary of State:
                        “O.K. J[ames] F. B[yrnes].”</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Baghdad</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-10-22T08:00:00+03:00"
                            >October 22, 1945—8 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 10:13 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>400. Instr 312, April 21.<note n="81" xml:id="d755fn81">Not printed.</note>
                    FonOff has asked whether any objection to release of Roosevelt letter dated
                    April 12 to Regent assuring “full consultation with both Arabs and Jews” re
                    Palestine.</p>
                <p>In view similarity with letter quoted Deptel 312, October 18,<note n="82"
                        xml:id="d755fn82">Not printed, but see footnote 70, <ref target="#pg_770">p.
                            770</ref>, and President Roosevelt’s letter of April 5 to King Ibn Saud,
                            <ref target="#pg_698">p. 698</ref>.</note> I told Foreign Office I
                    perceived no objection.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Moreland</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
